     `resp = client.post("<route>", json=json.loads(inputs_json))`.
   - For oracle "eq": `assert resp.status_code == 200` then `assert resp.json() == json.loads(expected_json)`.
   - For oracle "raises": `assert resp.status_code >= 400` (the HTTPException becomes a 4xx response).
   - Standard library + pytest + fastapi only. Output ONLY valid Python source.
